<topcClas>Trade, industry and markets - Industry and management</topcClas>       </subject>       <abstract><p>Abstract copyright UK Data Service and data collection copyright owner.</p>The <i>International Monetary Fund (IMF) World Economic Outlook (WEO)</i>  database contains selected macroeconomic data series from the statistical appendix of the World Economic Outlook report, which presents the IMF staff's analysis and projections of economic developments at the global level, in major country groups and in many individual countries. <br> <br> This database was first provided by the UK Data Service in November 2007. The UK Data Service web site includes further information on its <i>IMF WEO</i> holdings, including a <a href="http://ukdataservice.ac.uk//use-data/guides/dataset/weo.aspx" title="IMF World Economic Outlook dataset user guide">dataset user guide</a> and details of <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.5257/imf/weo/2011-09" title="IMF World Economic Outlook latest database updates ">latest database updates<a/>.<br> <br> <b>Citation:</b> The bibliographic citation for the database is: International Monetary Fund (<i>{YYYY}</i>): World Economic Outlook (<i>{date/edition of dataset}</i>). Mimas, University of Manchester. DOI: <i>{edition specific doi - e.g. <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.5257/imf/weo/2011-09">http://dx.doi.org/10.5257/imf/weo/2011-09</a>}</i>. <br> <br> <br> </abstract>       <abstract><B>Main Topics</B>:<br>Topics covered include:<ul/><li> national accounts</li><li>inflation</li><li> unemployment rates</li><li>balance of payments</li><li>debt</li><li>fiscal indicators</li><li>trade for countries and country groups (aggregates)</li><li>government finance</li><li>commodity prices</li></ul></abstract>       <sumDscr>         <timePrd>These data run from 1980 to the present and are updated every six months. The data include projections to 2018.</timePrd>         <collDate>Where the data are available, annual entries generally begin in 1980 and run to the latest available year.</collDate>
